Geoff Haigh, 61, from Oldham, Greater Manchester, wanted to marry long-term partner Heather after being diagnosed with terminal pancreatic cancer .
But guests at the couple's wedding were forced to listen to the song 'Wonderful Life' 10 times in a row due to a blunder .
Wedding certificate was recorded with the wrong date on, rendering it invalid .
Mr Haigh died weeks after the ceremony in November last year .